Description.note: Illustration: f. 7, full page miniature with architectural border of a king (originally Louis XI, now representing Francis I) enthroned and attended by his court. Modeled upon the manuscript of the original statutes painted by Jean Fouquet now Paris BNF fr. 19819, see F. Avril, pp 259-262. The miniature in the present manuscript is attributed to a painter in the circle of the Master of the Paris Entries, possibly Etienne Collaud.  The type of collar shown, consisting of a double strand of cockle shells, is the later form which had changed by 1520, see M. Orth, pp. 21-22, 31.
